From 44d378ef89e50ad7760ccf007d5c3369c6425141 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sergiy Shcherbyna <sergey.scherbina@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 15:57:32 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat(ui): fetchStreamSignal + intervalTick reactive
 primitives

Add two V1 UI-toolkit primitives, wired end-to-end for emit-spa SPAs,
mirroring fetchUrlSignal at every layer:

- fetchStreamSignal(name, url, body, tick, headers?): on mount/tick, POST
  url with the body signal value (application/json), then stream the
  response via r.body.getReader(), setting the signal to the ACCUMULATED
  decoded text on each chunk (OpenAI-style token streams; raw bytes, not
  SSE-parsed). Keeps last-good on error.
- intervalTick(name, ms): Int signal auto-incrementing every ms via
  setInterval; feeds a fetchUrlSignal tick to auto-poll.

Layers: primitives.ssc extern defs + exports; frontend FetchStreamSignal /
IntervalTick descriptor classes; FetchIntrinsics interpreter intrinsics;
JVM preamble + JvmRuntimeUiPrimitives lowering; signals.mjs builders
(_ssc_ui_fetchStreamSignal / _ssc_ui_intervalTick), _SignalText SSR render
(data-ssc-fetch-stream-url/-body/-tick/-headers, data-ssc-interval-ms),
_mountFetchStream / _mountInterval, collectSig + both mount walk paths;
JsGen capability detection.

Proven end-to-end: emit-spa -> headless Chrome. Stream signal accumulates
across 5 chunks to the full concatenation; POST body delivered server-side;
intervalTick increments 0..5 over ~3s.
